- Fixed Windows Fleet-maintained apps installing a duplicate copy at a different scope (per-user vs. per-machine), which left a stale copy behind and kept the patch policy reporting the host as not patched. Dual-variant Windows apps (including PowerToys, GIMP, VS Code, Chrome, Zoom, Dropbox, 1Password, Firefox, and others) now remove any opposite-scope copy before installing the managed copy, and all Windows Fleet-maintained apps now declare an explicit install scope.
